<subSubSection id="18278BDF96459E721EE59651D301534D" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C6A7219AEC367B8BB527967803937AAE" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F47546809E50844E514D545BA0BC12B4" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
The larva of 
<taxonomicName id="60FF282163D2C0E09EB62DCB47530975" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus martinus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinus">Epeorus martinus</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the following characteristics: pairs of moderately long acute submedian spines on the abdominal terga 1-9, large but narrow gill 1 forming a sucking disc and gill 7 being unfolded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7F27BCB14601614C70FA10875CEF81A1" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" type="habitat and biology">
<paragraph id="7F622D6D0A027B19B3CA61E4C11D5811" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Habitat and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="628ADAD0FA9BAA0145FA66D168FE5ADE" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
<taxonomicName id="AA69179CF6FB80B7F4C5E9256A60BF14" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus martinus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinus">Epeorus martinus</taxonomicName>
larvae are found in mountain streams with a moderate current, at an elevation of 300-2800 m (
<bibRefCitation id="7CF6F7B5EB62F6BE0C4417493B4EA1F6" author="Nguyen, VV" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology" pageId="27" pageNumber="88" pagination="19 - 28" title="Larvae of the heptageniid mayfly genus Epeorus (Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae) from Vietnam." volume="7" year="2004 a">Nguyen and Bae 2004a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4F42CFD318CB40573217DB312B06A2D1" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="6D1F4305D084BD857F4325AC5975E26F" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F277FB0E88BEED240E46EB07B21AF512" pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
<bibRefCitation id="0B5A688F6F08910C725ECE00AF619407" author="Webb, JM" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Arthropod Identification" pageId="28" pageNumber="89" pagination="1 - 55" title="Heptageniidae of the world. Part II. Key to the genera." volume="7" year="2008">Webb and McCafferty (2008)</bibRefCitation>
did not recognize the subgenera of 
<taxonomicName id="8FBB2805DDCC7056CCFEB618EB751BD2" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epeorus</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="4FE8E8A559B264AD7682CE2CC38023E8" authority="Chernova, 1981" authorityName="Chernova" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Belovius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Belovius" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Belovius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A6B0F1FDFC029FAE6F12A8689267BCFC" authority="Eaton, 1883" authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Iron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iron" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Iron</taxonomicName>
). However, we hold on the validity of subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="2641A5776EF155680CB0849347EF22E7" authority="Chernova, 1981" authorityName="Chernova" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Belovius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Belovius" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Belovius</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="74B698A7E0EB38E79B8EF5A26162EF1E" authority="Eaton, 1883" authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Iron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iron" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Iron</taxonomicName>
within genus 
<taxonomicName id="AD5D256E93C777D8E58163AF889F18BC" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epeorus</taxonomicName>
(Boonsoong &amp; Braasch, 2010). Therefore, we propose 
<taxonomicName id="DBB08CF8ECFA223BD5BD27355EA34F27" authority="Eaton, 1883" authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Iron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iron martinus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinus">Iron martinus</taxonomicName>
Braasch &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="B9DD5BE2625198300444329123C3C09A" originalValue="Soldán">Soldan</normalizedToken>
, 1984 = 
<taxonomicName id="65000A822BB52B30ADB43AAB36837C3D" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus (Iron) martinus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinus" subGenus="Iron">Epeorus (Iron) martinus</taxonomicName>
Braasch &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="8FA43FF344FBC3D184512AA12CFDDD2B" originalValue="Soldán">Soldan</normalizedToken>
, 1984
</paragraph>
